    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-13T12:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-13T12:36:00-05:00" n="1285"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1285">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115Am3/26.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-13T11:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 13, 1912—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Orozco has demanded of the El Paso representative of the American Smelters
                    Securities Co. [?] that they remake all checks to the National lines for month
                    of March, amounting to 26,000 pesos, to order of revolutionary government and
                    that all future payments for freight be made to same order.</p>
                <p>As this company’s interests are very large the precedent to be established is
                    very important. I am having the El Paso representative above mentioned
                    telegraphed to refuse immediate payment and to inform Orozco that he will be
                    held personally responsible by this Embassy for any damage done to American
                    lives and property. I request instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
